         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne Botanic Garden 25 Octob. ¶  ¶ 1872 ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ I have the honor to inform you that I have been instructed by my colleagues, the trustees of the Royal Park, at a meeting held this day, to ask...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.10.25</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To James Grant</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A345 Royal Park Zoological Society letter &amp; minute book, p.54, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne Botanic Garden 25 Octob.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1872</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to inform you that I have been instructed by my colleagues, the trustees of the Royal Park, at a meeting held this day, to ask you to grant them an interview, the trustees being anxious to bring verbally their views in reference to the permanent reservation of the Park before you. The trustees would regard it a particular favor if they could wait on you before Friday of next week, as one of our colleagues proceeds on that day to a distant part of the country.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">A meeting was offered<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">30 October in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">J. Lewis to M, 29 October 1872.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your obedient</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(signed) Ferd von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Secr. Trust. Roy. Park.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Honorable the President Board of Land &amp; Works<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to J. Grant, 1 November 1872</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>reported<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">a meeting of the Trustees had requested the Chairman of the meeting to communicate their views</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Royal Park had been<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">'</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">permanently reserved from sale</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">'</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>(<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Victoria government gazette</seg>, 25 March 1862, p. 529), but a portion had been sold<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(see M to J. MacPherson, 8 September 1870). Possibly as a result of the meeting,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in an order of 24 July 1873, the land was 'vested in the Board of Land and Works conjointly with the trustees of the said Park' (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Victoria government gazette</seg>, 8 August 1873, p. 1416).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
